# User Stories for Payment Processing Application

## 1. Authentication and User Management

### User Login

**Title:** User Login

**As a** registered user,  
**I want to** log in to the payment processing application,  
**So that** I can access my account and perform payment transactions securely.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Login screen with fields for username and password.
- Successful login directs to the application dashboard.
- Error message for incorrect credentials.
- Password reset functionality.
- Secure handling of login credentials (e.g., encryption).

**Scenario:**
- **Given** the user is on the login screen,  
  **When** they enter valid credentials and click "Login",  
  **Then** they should be directed to the application dashboard.

### User Logout

**Title:** User Logout

**As a** logged-in user,  
**I want to** log out of the application,  
**So that** my session is securely closed and no one else can access my account.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Logout button on the dashboard.
- Session termination and redirection to the login screen.

**Scenario:**
- **Given** the user is logged in,  
  **When** they click the logout button,  
  **Then** their session should be terminated and they should be redirected to the login screen.

### User Account Management

**Title:** Manage User Account

**As a** user,  
**I want to** view and manage my account settings,  
**So that** I can update my personal information and manage security settings.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Options to view and update personal details.
- Ability to change password and manage security settings (e.g., two-factor authentication).
- Confirmation of saved changes.

**Scenario:**
- **Given** the user is on the account settings page,  
  **When** they update their personal information and click "Save",  
  **Then** the changes should be saved and confirmed.

## 2. Payment Processing

### Select Target Account

**Title:** Select Target Account

**As a** logged-in user,  
**I want to** select a target account for the payment,  
**So that** I can specify where the payment should be directed.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- List of available accounts.
- Selection and confirmation of the target account.

**Scenario:**
- **Given** the user is on the payment page,  
  **When** they select an account from the list,  
  **Then** the details of the selected account should be displayed.

### Select Medium of Payment

**Title:** Select Medium of Payment

**As a** user,  
**I want to** choose the medium of payment,  
**So that** I can use the appropriate method to complete the transaction.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Options for different payment mediums (e.g., bank transfer, credit card, e-wallet).
- Selection and validation of the chosen payment medium.

**Scenario:**
- **Given** the user is on the payment medium selection screen,  
  **When** they choose a payment method,  
  **Then** the application should display the relevant fields for entering payment details.

### Enter Payment Details

**Title:** Enter Payment Details

**As a** user,  
**I want to** enter the details of the payment,  
**So that** I can specify the amount and other necessary information to complete the transaction.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Fields to enter payment amount and additional details.
- Validation of entered details.
- Option to review details before submission.

**Scenario:**
- **Given** the user has selected a payment medium,  
  **When** they enter the payment amount and details,  
  **Then** they should be able to review and confirm the payment information.

### Obtain Payment Confirmation

**Title:** Obtain Payment Confirmation

**As a** user,  
